<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Bigtable on MCP Toolbox for Databases</title><link>https://dishaprakash.github.io/genai-toolbox/v0.14.0/resources/tools/bigtable/</link><description>Recent content in Bigtable on MCP Toolbox for Databases</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://dishaprakash.github.io/genai-toolbox/v0.14.0/resources/tools/bigtable/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>bigtable-sql</title><link>https://dishaprakash.github.io/genai-toolbox/v0.14.0/resources/tools/bigtable/bigtable-sql/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://dishaprakash.github.io/genai-toolbox/v0.14.0/resources/tools/bigtable/bigtable-sql/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="about">About&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>A &lt;code>bigtable-sql&lt;/code> tool executes a pre-defined SQL statement against a Bigtable
instance. It&amp;rsquo;s compatible with any of the following sources:&lt;/p>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>&lt;a href="../../../genai-toolbox/v0.14.0/resources/sources/bigtable/">bigtable&lt;/a>&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;h3 id="googlesql">GoogleSQL&lt;/h3>
&lt;p>Bigtable supports SQL queries. The integration with Toolbox supports &lt;code>googlesql&lt;/code>
dialect, the specified SQL statement is executed as a &lt;a href="https://cloud.google.com/bigtable/docs/googlesql-overview">data manipulation
language (DML)&lt;/a> statements, and specified parameters will
inserted according to their name: e.g. &lt;code>@name&lt;/code>.&lt;/p>
